Andreas Gruenbacher <agruen@suse.de> wrote:
> 
> static inline void swap(void *a, void *b, int size)
> {
>        if (size % sizeof(long)) {
>                char t;
>                do {
>                        t = *(char *)a;
>                        *(char *)a++ = *(char *)b;
>                        *(char *)b++ = t;
>                } while (--size > 0);
>        } else {
>                long t;
>                do {
>                        t = *(long *)a;
>                        *(long *)a = *(long *)b;
>                        *(long *)b = t;
>                        size -= sizeof(long);
>                } while (size > sizeof(long));
>        }
> }
What if a/b aren't aligned?
